FBIS4-11277 "drlat080_a_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-080 Daily Report 25 Apr 1994 CARIBBEAN Cuba Meets Fidel Castro at Airport Meets Fidel Castro at Airport FL2604002994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 2300 GMT 25 Apr 94 FL2604002994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [By Julio Gomes Yosia from Jose Marti International Airport] [Excerpts] Aboard DC-10 Flight 741, following a stopover in Madrid, Zambian President Frederick Chiluba has just arrived in Cuba for an official, friendly visit at the invitation of Commander in Chief Fidel Castro who at this moment is walking toward the plane to meet the illustrious visitor and his retinue. [passage omitted] The Zambian president at this moment is being greeted by our commander in chief and by other Politburo members. This is an exclusive direct report from Jose Marti International Airport on the arrival of Zambian President Frederick Chiluba on Flight 741 aboard a DC-10 plane. [passage omitted] [Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks broadcast in Spanish at 0000 GMT on 26 April shows Cuban President Fidel Castro walking toward Zambian President Frederick Chiluba as the latter disembarks from his plane. Castro is seen embracing the African leader. They then slowly walk side by side from the plane.]
